BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:izRQmtGRt3xU3ryFgzulb
SUMMARY:Restoration Event | Pioneer Park
DTSTAMP:20260306T011841Z
DTSTART:20260307T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy the towering trees\, listen to the birds\, and give a lit
	tle back to this beautiful park by removing common ivy that is taking over
	  the understory of Pioneer Park's SE quadrant. It will be a great chance 
	t o get your hands in the dirt\, learn about native plants and our local f
	orests\, and work alongside neighbors and friends!\n\nAll ages welcome\, a
	nd no experience necessary! Gloves\, tools\, water\, and small snacks prov
	ided. Please note: we require participants aged 14 and under to volunteer 
	 with a parent or guardian at a ratio of 1 adult to 3 kids.\n\nWhen: Satur
	d ay\, March 7th\, 10am-1pm\n\nWhere: Pioneer Park SE\, follow volunteer e
	vent signs\n\nWhat to bring: Dress for the weather in clothes you don't mi
	nd get ting dirty \\(think: long pants\, boots or sneakers\\). Bring water
	. Small snacks\, gloves\, and tools will be provided.\n\nRegistration: htt
	ps://volunteersignup.org/CWRCR\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/de
	tails/restoration-event-pioneer-park/18066420/2026-03-07T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-pioneer
	-park/18066420/2026-03-07T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:OaReEQvzNgJodqXtABRmT
SUMMARY:WA Concealed Carry Class at Wildlife Committee of
DTSTAMP:20260306T011841Z
DTSTART:20260308T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:This 4-hour comprehensive training course is designed to educat
	e individuals on the laws and regulations surrounding the carrying of conc
	ealed firearms. This class covers essential topics such as the use of forc
	e\, firearms safety\, and the proper handling and storage of firearms\, as
	 well as the specific laws and any requirements for obtaining permits in W
	ashington\, Oregon\, Arizona\, and Utah. Upon completion of the class\, at
	tendees will be eligible to apply for the above-mentioned permits. You wil
	l also receive a WA - HB-1143 Gun Safety Certificate. DATES and TIMES are 
	subject to change\, please view our website for the most up to date and ac
	curate class info. https://www.legalheat.com/classes/in-person/concealed-c
	arry-class-at-wildlife-committee-of-washington-bothell-wa/?utm\\_source=fa
	cebook&utm\\_medium=event\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details
	/wa-concealed-carry-class-at-wildlife-committee-of/18252325/2026-03-08T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/wa-concealed-carry-class-
	at-wildlife-committee-of/18252325/2026-03-08T00
LOCATION:Wildlife Committee of Washington - WCWShootingSports - Kenmore Ran
	ge\, 1031 228th St SW\, Bothell\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
